item.description:
SML REPL in Spacemacs After installing sml and adding a sml layer in my spacemacs, I typed C-c-C-s or M-x sml RET, a sml REPL did not show up. An error message showed up instead:
{% codeblock lang:sh %} sml: no such file or directory {% endcodeblock %}
But I could type sml to start a sml REPL in my terminal. It turned out I should add the sml path to my emacs.
